{
  "text": "The XRD test was performed to prove the phase formed after the 1100\u2070C sintering process. Figure 7 shows the phase formed on the 5% and 10% were of Austenite (\u03b3), Ferrite (\u03b1), and manganese oxide (MnO2). MnO2 showed that some of the manganese reacts with oxygen and does not diffuse into the Fe matrix. This manganese oxide phase is formed because the manganese evaporated form Mn vapor at temperature 400\u2070C-1200\u2070C. This manganese vapor diffused into the iron matrix by the solid-gas process. [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "135581703"
